fingermiddleleft.label: Finger Ranges of Motion Figures 16-21 page 461, 16-23 page 463, 16-25 page 464: AMA Estimated Normal: DIP Flexion (70D) DIP Extension (0D), PIP Flexion (100D) PIP Extension (0D), MP Flexion (90D) MP Extension (+20D). Motion is measured with goniometer and is reported right over left side in Degrees (D).
fingermiddleleft.textareatext: Hyper-extension is measured with a '+' preceeding the measurement. i.e. +10 = 10 degrees of hyper-extension.

fingermiddleleft.label: Actual goniometer measurements of the range of motion are only required for PR-4 (Permanent & Stationary) reports. Visual estimates of the range of motion may be adequate for Doctor's First reports and PR-2 reports.
Triggering
options: Mild - Inconsistent triggering during active range of motion
Moderate - Constant triggering during active range of motion
Severe-Constant triggering during passive range of motion
